The Journal of Consumer Psychology is a quarterly peer-reviewed academic journal covering psychology as it relates to consumer behavior. It was established in 1992 and is published by Elsevier on behalf of the Society for Consumer Psychology, the 23rd division of the American Psychological Association. The editor-in-chief is Amna Kirmani (University of Maryland, College Park). According to the Journal Citation Reports, the journal has a 2015 impact factor of 2.009.


